"{\"description\":\"Team Leader [Welding] in Reading, GB\",\"howToApply\":\"To apply, click 'apply now' and submit your application by 7th December 2023. Please note that some on-call work may be required for this Maintenance Grade role. The assessment process will consist of a competency and technical interview. All candidates will be required to undergo and pass a drugs and alcohol test. We are an equal opportunity employer and value diversity. Diversity and inclusion are a priority for us, and we are committed to providing a welcoming and safe environment for everyone. If you require any reasonable adjustments/modifications to support your application, please include a note in your application. All offers of employment are conditional upon satisfactory completion of pre-employment checks.\",\"aboutTheRole\":{\"essential\":[\"Experience of organising and controlling the safe and efficient delivery of work\",\"Excellent communication skills, both in person and in writing\",\"Knowledge of discipline-specific maintenance, inspection, faulting, and renewal techniques\",\"Knowledge of relevant standards, procedures, and instructions\",\"A clear and inspirational leader with a strong sense of direction\"],\"desirable\":[\"Hold or be working towards an NVQ level 2 or 3 (or equivalent) in a relevant subject or have attained the appropriate level of knowledge gained through equivalent relevant experience\",\"Able and willing to drive vehicles as required by business need\"],\"keyAccountabilities\":[\"Establishing appropriate safety arrangements and ensuring compliance with safe systems of work\",\"Controlling and checking the quality of work and the competence of staff\",\"Compiling vital reports\",\"Directing, organizing, and motivating a high-performing team\"]}}"